-- Barclays names Jones, Nakai as co-CEOs for Asia Pacific
-- By Lawrence White
-- Thu May 01, 2014 11:19PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, May 2 (Reuters) - Barclays PLC <BARC.L> has named Andrew Jones and Eiji Nakai as co-chief executive officers for Asia Pacific, replacing the retiring Robert Morrice.

The appointments are subject to regulatory approval, the UK-based bank said in a statement on Friday. Jones, currently the region's chief operating officer, joined the bank in 2000 and has worked in Hong Kong and Singapore in fixed income and corporate finance roles.